{"_path":"/html","_dir":"","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"HTML","description":"Initial guidance for working with Hypertext Markup Language","navTitle":"HTML","position":1,"category":"HTML, front-end","date":"2017-05-03","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"html"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"HTML"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"HTML should be prepared using a template language.\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"/pug"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Pug"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is recommended for static files."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Some variance from the below guidance is expected\nif using a framework to generate HTML from reactive\nor shadow-DOM data (for attribute order and boolean\nattributes for example). However given that overall on a\nproject the goal is consistency this should be documented\nand monitored along those lines."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"syntax"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Syntax"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"content-list","props":{"icon":"heroicons-outline:check-circle"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use two spaces for indentation"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use single quotation marks for attributes"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Don't repeat IDs in a document"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"encoding"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Encoding"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"content-list","props":{"icon":"heroicons-outline:check-circle"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Use UTF-8 encoding and custom characters instead of HTML entities."}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"attributes"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Attributes"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"content-list","props":{"icon":"heroicons-outline:check-circle"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Omit "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":""},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"type"}]},{"type":"text","value":" attributes in CSS and JavaScript"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Omit values in boolean attributes"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Comply to the following attribute order ...\n"},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"class"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"id, name"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"data-*"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"src, for, type, href, value"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"title, alt"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"role, aria-*"}]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"nesting"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Nesting"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"HTML Tags should be properly nested per the document specification.\nIncorrectly nested tags are usually not a problem if a templating language\nis used to generate HTML but can emerge if fragmented HTML is delivered from\nmultiple partials."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ideally run pages through the "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://validator.w3.org/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"W3C markup validation service"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\nas part of build. This will reveal issues immediately."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"accessibility"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Accessibility"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Projects must meet AA checkpoints from "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"WCAG 2.1 standards"}]},{"type":"text","value":",\nand where possible, we should aim for support of AAA checkpoints."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Full guidelines on implementation of accessible markup is outside the scope\nof this document. The "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://wave.webaim.org/extension/","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"WAVE tool from WebAIM"}]},{"type":"text","value":" is a good way to audit\nyour sites. Careful consideration should be given to the introduction of\nsome audit tooling in the build process. WAVE is good for manual tests but\nAxe and a11y in Storybook can also assist in testing and automation. Axe also\nprovide a linter plug-in for VS Code."}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"html","depth":2,"text":"HTML","children":[{"id":"syntax","depth":3,"text":"Syntax"},{"id":"encoding","depth":3,"text":"Encoding"},{"id":"attributes","depth":3,"text":"Attributes"},{"id":"nesting","depth":3,"text":"Nesting"},{"id":"accessibility","depth":3,"text":"Accessibility"}]}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:3.html.md","_source":"content","_file":"3.html.md","_extension":"md"}